cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper deals with machine learning tasks that involve sampling a subset of items from a collection based on a parameterized distribution. It proposes a continuous relaxation of subset sampling that provides reparameterization gradients, which is relevant to the field of deep learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
